{{Redirect|Shares||Share (disambiguation){{!}}Share}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2016}}{{Securities}}
In [[finance|financial markets]], a '''share''' is a unit used as [[mutual fund]]s, [[limited partnership]]s, and [[real estate investment trust]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.investopedia.com/terms/s/shares.asp|title=Shares Definition|publisher=[[Investopedia]]|last1=Chen|first1=James|date=February 23, 2018|accessdate=9 July 2013}}</ref> The owner of shares in the company is a [[shareholder]] (or stockholder) of the corporation.<ref>{{cite book|last=Hoang|first=Paul|title=Business and Management|publisher=IBID Press|location=Victoria|year=2007|pages=[https://archive.org/details/businessmanageme0000hoan/page/71 71]|chapter=1.4 Stakeholders|isbn=1-876659-63-7|url=https://archive.org/details/businessmanageme0000hoan/page/71}}</ref>  A share is an indivisible unit of capital, expressing the ownership relationship between the company and the shareholder.

